<TITLE> Patal gets bail in tax-dodge case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 28 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court granted former BNP state minister Fazlur Rahman Patal bail in a tax evasion case. Dhaka metropolitan senior special judge ANM Bashirullah gave the order on Sunday after the ex-minister turned himself in to the court with a bail plea. The court on Mar 1 issued an arrest warrant against Patal in the case accusing the BNP leader of evading income tax on concealed wealth. The High Court on Mar 8 ordered Patal to surrender before the court within eight weeks. Judge Bashirullah set Apr 13 for charge framing in the case and sent the documents to the Special Judges Court 1. b
